  "revisionSemantics": "revision is a per-event monotonic-increasing integer the server assigns on each accepted mutation. The client applies a response only if its revision is greater than the highest already applied for that event; a stale/out-of-order response (revision <= applied) is discarded. A pending mutation with no response within the client budget is rolled back, so the UI never sticks in pending.",
